description: From Latin stem, mur-, of mus (“mouse”) + -ine.

adjectives.description: murine (comparative more murine, superlative most murine)

entries.meaning: Of, pertaining to, or characteristic of a mouse.
More generally, of, pertaining to, or characteristic of any rodent up to the taxonomic rank of Muroidea, most often with reference to mice and rats of the subfamily Murinae.
examples: Are our stem cells really, then, a billion or a trillion times more "cancerproof" than murine stem cells?
